# UPDATE 0.4.7\n\n## Weather Settings\nIntroducing weather physics with snow, rain, and wind. You can enable any weather on any map in private, solo, and practice modes. However only some of the maps allow weather in public matches. Weather affects ball physics such as drag on the field. Weather is synced for all players in the same lobby and is set by the lobby creator.\n\n## New Starting Arena\nExplore the next-gen starting stadium, which will evolve with crowds and additional features in the future. It\u2019s also available in multiplayer.\n\n## Replays Auto Highlights\nEnable automatic goal highlights when watching replays.\n\n## New 1v1 Elo Interface\nCheck out the overall 1v1 Elo chart and use the new \"Find Opponent\" button for quick matches. \n\n## Referee Tools\nUse marking spray, yellow cards, and red cards. Press (A) to switch tools when in the ref mode. \n\n## New Scoreboards Designs\nChoose from various scoreboard designs for custom arenas.\n\n## Vote Kick\nNow available in public lobbies.\n\n## Camera Device Follow Mode\nNew interface, better performance, and the \"Follow Me\" mode for the camera device.\n\n## Scoreboards On Custom Arena Goals\nDisplay goal counters on custom arena goals (press settings on the goal when editing your arena).\n\n## Wind Physics Test Bundle\nIncludes 2 special effect balls created during weather physics development.\n\n## Other\nStore Credits item for custom arenas, performance optimizations, updated tutorial, fixed known bugs. \n\n## Free Collectible 2025 Ball\nFind it in the store at the new starting stadium. It will be removed after New Year\u2019s. \n", "created_date": 1734707010, "id": "27947270308220840", "version": "0.1", "version_code": 270, "release_status": "RELEASED", "status": "APPROVED", "binary_test_results": {"nodes": []}, "obb_binary": null, "asset_files": {"count": 0}, "debug_symbols": {"count": 0}, "__isAppBinaryWithFileAsset": "AndroidBinary"}]}}, "viewer": {"user": null}}}